Q: How to have primitive discard additional arguments A: <p>We could use global <code>options()</code>. However – as MrFlick stated in his answer – primitives' args can't be changed without cost of copying.</p>
<pre><code>&gt; x &lt;- c(1, 2, 3, 4, NA, 6, 7)
&gt; 
&gt; ## expand args of method (here default)
&gt; formals(mean.default)$na.rm &lt;- substitute(getOption('na.rm', default=FALSE))
&gt; 
&gt; ## impossible for primitive, so copy
&gt; sum2 &lt;- function(x, na.rm=getOption('na.rm', FALSE)) {
+   if(na.rm) x &lt;- x[!is.na(x)]
+   base::sum(x)
+ }
&gt; 
&gt; oo &lt;- options(na.rm=TRUE)  ## set options
&gt; 
&gt; sapply(list(mean=mean, sum=sum2, n=length), \(f) f(x))
     mean       sum         n 
 3.833333 23.000000  7.000000 
&gt; 
&gt; options(oo)  ## reset
&gt; ## oo &lt;- options(na.rm=FALSE)  ## or
&gt; 
&gt; sapply(list(mean=mean, sum=sum2, n=length), \(f) f(x))
mean  sum    n 
  NA   NA    7 
</code></pre>

Q: LinkedIn organizationPageStatistics API returns 400 PARAM_INVALID for timeIntervals (REST.li 2.0) A: <p>Neither of your attempts appear to result in valid and appropriate JSON. Have you tried</p>
<pre><code>
params = {
    &quot;q&quot;: &quot;organization&quot;,
    &quot;organization&quot;: organization_urn,
    &quot;timeIntervals&quot;:{
       &quot;timeGranularityType&quot;: &quot;DAY&quot;,
       &quot;timeRange&quot;:{
          &quot;start&quot;: start_ms,
          &quot;end&quot;: end_ms
       }
     }
}

</code></pre>
<p>You'll need to ensure that you get the correct values for <code>start_ms</code> and <code>end_ms</code> in there. I'm also not sure how using a granularity of <code>DAY</code> will work with start and end times in <code>milliseconds</code></p>
